RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 23 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REALITOS broke out and was corrected quickly, moved up to take the lead, set a relaxed pace from the rail, was challenged by another foe at the quarter pole, repelled that foe and drew off for the easy win. MYLIES STAR broke outward and was straightened up quickly, settled mid pack in company with another foe, moved up around the three eighths pole, shifted out down the lane and closed really well, was able to pass rivals and obtain the place spot. DEBS PRAYER traveled on the outside several lengths off the leader, was in contention in the turn, asked at the quarter pole, closed well but wasn't enough to catch the leader today. B B GUN BULLSEYE traveled into the first turn on the lead with another foe from the three path, rated just off the leader until the half, started to challenge for the lead in the turn, was matching stride for the lead coming out of the turn, faltered in the lane. GUANAJUATO was along the rail in the first turn, was brought out three wide down the back side, was shifted five wide in the lane but stopped. ZEEROCK off slow and trailed throughout.

HOORAY AUSTIN shied mildly from a quicker-breaking outer rival at the start, but bumped an inner foe in the process, tracked in the five path, chased the four path and outside of rivals around the turn, and faded. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARTIER CAT tracked from midpack along the inside, pursued from the pocket in the two path behind the leaders around the far turn, inched closer between horses entering the lane, produced a bid inside of the leader at the three sixteenths pole, led entering the final furlong, and held from an outer chaser. GOLDEN PEGASUS took a bump from an inner rival at the start, tracked in midpack three wide, was urged to inch closer in the four path around the far turn, came into the lane within striking distance, but was subtly outkicked by an inner rival in upper stretch, chased that foe home well through the final furlong, vied nearing the wire, but missed. DUKE OF BLUE RIDGE leaned out and bumped an outer rival at the start, prompted the pace along the inside, backed off and shifted out to stalk outside of the leader entering the backstretch, tugged while well in the bit before bidding entering the far turn, led in the three path at the three furlong pole, but was outkicked by an inner rival in upper stretch, and yielded between horses in the final furlong. STOCKPILER trailed two wide, took the far turn in the five path before fanning into the lane in the seven path, and stayed on willingly. LIONS NOT SHEEP stalked two to three wide around the first turn, but faded between horses approaching the three furlong pole, got floated to the six path while between horses at the quarter pole, and yet came again, but failed to reach contention. MAGAZINE STREET was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, lacked speed two wide, saved ground around the far turn, shifted five wide in upper stretch, but lacked a rally between horses. ENDLESS SUNSET saved ground far back, but to no avail. UNCLE NICK set the pace in the two path, but was headed by an outer rival at the three furlong pole, and weakened in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RALLY BOARD broke the fastest, was allowed to find his stride early, rated off the leader, moved before the three eighths pole, was in control within a few strides, went to work at the quarter pole and dominated this field. SLICK AND FAST broke awkwardly while off a step slow, saved ground off of the pace, retreated to trail at the half mile pole, shifted off of the fence turning for home, then to the seven path in upper stretch, then chased evenly outside of the leader, and missed reaching place.
